core HTTP utilities for Eclipse Jetty, including request and response metadata, headers, cookies, MIME types, and URI handling. It is used by Jetty server and client components to parse, represent, and generate HTTP protocol data.\",\nmetadata/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-http/index.json:94:    \"description\" : \"Jetty HTTP provides core HTTP utilities for Eclipse Jetty, including request and response metadata, headers, cookies, MIME types, and URI handling. It is used by Jetty server and client components to parse, represent, and generate HTTP protocol data.\",\nmetadata/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-http/index.json:115:    \"description\" : \"Jetty HTTP provides core HTTP utilities for Eclipse Jetty, including request and response metadata, headers, cookies, MIME types, and URI handling. It is used by Jetty server and client components to parse, represent, and generate HTTP protocol data.\",\nmetadata/org.osgi/osgi.annotation/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"osgi.annotation is the OSGi Release 8 aggregate annotation artifact used when compiling OSGi bundles. It packages bundle and versioning annotations for declaring manifest headers, requirements, capabilities, exports, package versions, and provider or consumer API roles in source code.\",\nmetadata/org.osgi/osgi.annotation/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"osgi.annotation is the OSGi Release 7 aggregate annotation artifact used when compiling OSGi bundles. It packages bundle and versioning annotations for declaring manifest headers, requirements, capabilities, exports, package versions, and provider or consumer API roles in source code.\",\nmetadata/org.http4s/http4s-core_3/1.0.0-M44/reachability-metadata.json:35:        \"typeReached\": \"org.http4s.headers.Content$minusRange$\"\nmetadata/org.http4s/http4s-core_3/1.0.0-M44/reachability-metadata.json:41:        \"typeReached\": \"org.http4s.headers.Content$minusType$\"\nmetadata/org.http4s/http4s-core_3/1.0.0-M44/reachability-metadata.json:47:        \"typeReached\": \"org.http4s.headers.Cookie$\"\nmetadata/org.http4s/http4s-core_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"http4s-core_3 provides the core Scala 3 HTTP model and abstractions for building functional HTTP clients and servers, including requests, responses, headers, routes, entities, and related syntax. It is the foundation used by http4s client and server modules while integrating with Cats Effect and FS2 for effectful and streaming HTTP programs.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-gson/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Provides Gson-based JSON serialization and deserialization support for the JJWT library. When present on the runtime classpath, it lets JJWT automatically use Gson to process JWT headers and claims.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-gson/index.json:29:    \"description\" : \"Provides Gson-based JSON serialization and deserialization support for the JJWT library. When present on the runtime classpath, it lets JJWT automatically use Gson to process JWT headers and claims.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/index.json:10:    \"description\" : \"jjwt-jackson provides Jackson-based JSON serializer and deserializer implementations for JJWT. It lets JJWT encode JWT headers and claims to JSON and parse them back using Jackson.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/index.json:25:    \"description\" : \"jjwt-jackson provides Jackson-based JSON serializer and deserializer implementations for JJWT. It lets JJWT encode JWT headers and claims to JSON and parse them back using Jackson.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/index.json:45:    \"description\" : \"jjwt-jackson provides Jackson-based JSON serializer and deserializer implementations for JJWT. It lets JJWT encode JWT headers and claims to JSON and parse them back using Jackson.\",\nmetadata/com.typesafe.akka/akka-parsing_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Akka Parsing provides Akka HTTP's internal parsing toolkit, including the parboiled2-based parser DSL and supporting parser input, rule, and error-formatting utilities. It underpins Akka HTTP's HTTP message parsing so higher-level modules can parse requests, responses, headers, and related protocol data efficiently.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/index.json:12:    \"description\": \"The jjwt-orgjson module provides JJWT's org.json-based serializer and deserializer so JWT headers and claims can be read and written using JSON-Java. It is the recommended JSON backend for Android applications and supports simple object-to-JSON marshaling instead of POJO unmarshalling.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/index.json:28:    \"description\": \"The jjwt-orgjson module provides JJWT's org.json-based serializer and deserializer so JWT claims and headers can be read and written using JSON-Java. It is the recommended JSON backend for Android applications and supports simple object-to-JSON marshaling rather than POJO unmarshalling.\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-server-content-negotiation-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Ktor Server ContentNegotiation is the server-side Ktor plugin for negotiating request and response media types with Accept and Content-Type headers. It registers content converters so Kotlin/JVM server applications can deserialize incoming request bodies and serialize outgoing responses for formats such as JSON, XML, CBOR, and ProtoBuf.\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-client-content-negotiation-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Ktor client ContentNegotiation adds a client plugin for negotiating request and response media types with Accept and Content-Type headers. It registers content converters so Kotlin/JVM clients can serialize outgoing bodies and deserialize incoming responses for formats such as JSON, XML, CBOR, and ProtoBuf.\",\nmetadata/com.lihaoyi/requests_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Requests-Scala is a Scala HTTP client inspired by Python Requests for making synchronous HTTP calls from JVM applications. It wraps Java networking APIs with a small Scala interface for building requests, sending request bodies, handling headers and authentication, and reading responses.\",\nmetadata/org.eclipse.microprofile.openapi/microprofile-openapi-api/4.1.1/reachability-metadata.json:89:          \"org.eclipse.microprofile.openapi.models.headers.Header\"\nmetadata/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/rest-assured/rest-assured/$version$/rest-assured-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/rest-assured/rest-assured\",\nmetadata/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/rest-assured/rest-assured/tree/rest-assured-$version$/rest-assured/src/test\",\nmetadata/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/rest-assured/rest-assured/$version$/rest-assured-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"REST Assured provides a Java DSL for testing and validating REST services. It supports constructing HTTP requests, extracting responses, and asserting status codes, headers, bodies, and serialization behavior in integration and API tests.\",\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-codec-stomp/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Netty Codec STOMP provides Netty encoders, decoders, frame types, headers, and aggregators for the STOMP messaging protocol. It lets Netty-based clients and servers parse and produce STOMP frames over asynchronous network channels.\",\nmetadata/com.shapesecurity/salvation2/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Salvation2 is a Java library for parsing, representing, validating, manipulating, and rendering Content Security Policy headers. It helps applications inspect what a CSP policy allows or restricts and report policy mistakes, deprecated features, and nonstandard directives.\",\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-codec-haproxy/index.json:10:    \"description\" : \"Netty Codec HAProxy provides encoders, decoders, and message model classes for the HAProxy PROXY protocol in Netty pipelines. It lets Netty-based servers and clients parse and emit proxy protocol headers so original client connection metadata can be preserved through load balancers and proxies.\",\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-codec-haproxy/index.json:79:    \"description\" : \"Netty Codec HAProxy provides encoders, decoders, and message model classes for the HAProxy PROXY protocol in Netty pipelines. It lets Netty-based servers and clients parse and emit proxy protocol headers so original client connection metadata can be preserved through load balancers and proxies.\",\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778450133850}}
